  "text": "The ultrasound beam intensity and pressure profiles were modeled using Field II (http://fieldii.dk/), a well characterized ultrasound simulation tool [CITATION_1] . The example code provided by the designer for producing intensity and pressure profiles, calc_int.m, was modified for the specific transducer specifications and settings used in this study: transducer center frequency (10 Mz), transducer radius (9.525 mm), focal length (19.05 mm), cycles per pulse [CITATION_2] , pulse repetition frequency (7.5 kHz), number of elements (1). The transducer aperture was modeled using the function xdc_concave. The intensity was set to 202 W/m 2 in order to match the peak pressure 2.5MPa to that which was measured with the hydrophone. The program then generated simulated beam intensity and pressure profiles.",
